strategies: i tried to tie things together in my mind by associating them to things I know. Like for the cactus I tied it to the buffalo because they both reminds me of Texas. For the potato and the skis I thought of french fries when people area learning to ski.
easier: Yes the ones that I could associate in my mind were easier than the ones that I couldn't come up with a good relation for. For example the fish I couldn't connect it it kept confusing me. The leaves and the trees were easy because they were both plants. The train and the ferris wheel were easy because they were both rides. The canoe and the skis I had to think of them as being on top of a car for travel. The fish was really hard to place.
comments: It was actually kind of more difficult than I expected it to be. For some reason when I had to make a path to things I was drawing a blank at times where I wasn't sure if the connection I was trying to make was too drawn out. It wasn't boring but the yellow blue choices did make it harder to focus on the image pairs.
